Interface DimensionsArObject

All Superinterfaces:
DimensionsObject
All Known Subinterfaces:
Baseline, BaseRequest, DimensionsLcObject, FileArea, Group, IDMRequest, ItemRevision, Part, Project, RepositoryFolder, Request, RequestAttachment, RequestList, Requirement, SecRequest, User, WorkingCMRequestList, WorkingIDMRequestList
public interface DimensionsArObject
extends DimensionsObject

Represents a Dimensions object that has attributes and relationships to other objects and has user-defined attributes. Extends the dmpmcli DimensionsObject interface, which has no methods.

A note about sensitive attributes

When calling updateAttribute(int), if the attribute in question has been marked as sensitive, authorization point information will be required. If it has not been supplied in the form of an attribute, an exception will be thrown. This method will then only be satisfied if the correct authorization point information has been supplied in the system attribute AUTHORIZATION_POINT_INFO. The code below is an example of how to cope with this situation for a single request:

        Request req = (Request) reqs.get(i);
        int sensitiveAttributeNumber = ...
        req.setAttribute(sensitiveAttributeNumber, "a new value");
        boolean authReqd, authFailed, succeeded = false;
        int attempts = 0;
        while (!succeeded & attempts < 3) { // you shouldn't actually need to impose this check, the server will only allow 3 attempts
                try {
                        req.updateAttribute(sensitiveAttrNum);
                        succeeded = true;
                } catch (AuthorizationRequiredException are) {
                        authReqd = true;
                } catch (AuthorizationFailedException afe) {
                        authFailed = true;
                } finally {
                        if (authReqd) {
                                authReqd = false;
                                req.setAttribute(SystemAttributes.AUTHORIZATION_POINT_INFO, "incorrect_password"); // this could come from a GUI
                        } else if (authFailed) {
                                authFailed = false;
                                req.setAttribute(SystemAttributes.AUTHORIZATION_POINT_INFO, "correct_password"); // this could come from a GUI
                        }
                }
                attempts++;
        }

For multiple objects, it is advisable to set the AUTHORIZATION_POINT_INFO attribute on all of them before calling updateAttribute(). This will allow a bulk calling of updateAttribute() to take place without an exception being thrown for each one.

The server allows 3 unsuccessful attempts at updating a sensitive attribute, after which it will fail silently.

queryAttribute

void queryAttribute(int attrNum)
Populate a Dimensions attribute in this object.

Provides a hint that you may be asking for this attribute very soon, so it should be retrieved from the database (or updated if it is already retrieved and cached).

The following type rules apply to attribute values; 1/ if the attribute is of type AttributeDataType.CHAR, a java.lang.String is returned. 2/ if the attribute is of type AttributeDataType.DATE, a java.lang.String is returned, an attempt to parse it as a java.util.Date can be made using the convenience method DimensionsUtils.parseDate(String). 3/ if the attribute is of type AttributeDataType.INTEGER, a java.lang.Integer is returned, or null if not set. This is used only for system attributes. 4/ if the attribute is of type AttributeDataType.NUMBER, a java.lang.String is returned, it may be possible to parse into a double for sorting purposes.

Parameters:
attrNum - the attribute number to query.
See Also:
SystemAttributes

getAttribute

java.lang.Object getAttribute(int attrNum)
Retrieve a Dimensions attribute value from this object's internal cache. If this object's internal cache is not populated with the value of the attribute (by calling queryAttribute) then the method will return null. Note that this method can also return null as the attribute value for some attributes (e.g. if the value is not set in the database) even after queryAttribute has been called.

Parameters:
attrNum - the attribute number to get.
Returns:
the value of the specified attribute.
See Also:
SystemAttributes

getAttribute

java.util.List getAttribute(int[] attrNums)
Retrieves a set of Dimensions attribute values from this object's internal cache. If this object's internal cache is not populated with the value of a certain attribute (by calling queryAttribute) then the method will return a null value for this attribute in the list. Note that this method can also return null as attribute values for some attributes (e.g. if the value is not set in the database) even after queryAttribute has been called.

Parameters:
attrNums - the set of attributes to get.
Returns:
the list of attribute values in the same order as the input list of attribute numbers.
See Also:
SystemAttributes

                         boolean child)

Part.class

Project.class

Parameters:

child - whether child or parent objects cache should be deleted
